The normalize() method returns the Unicode Normalization Form of a given string. The form will be the Normalization Form Canonical Composition.

difference

  • difference(first: string, second: string, maxLenDelta?: number): number
    • Defined in strings.ts:536

    Computes the difference score for two strings. More similar strings have a higher score. We use largest common subsequence dynamic programming approach but penalize in the end for length differences. Strings that have a large length difference will get a bad default score 0. Complexity - both time and space O(first.length * second.length) Dynamic programming LCS computation http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Longest_common_subsequence_problem

    Parameters

    • first: string

      a string

    • second: string

      a string

    • Default value maxLenDelta: number = 4

    Returns number
